The paper discusses the use of massive MIMO in real propagation environments and investigates the possibility of reducing the required number of RF chains by performing antenna selection. This involves optimizing the use of antennas to increase spectral and transmit-energy efficiency. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
